The paper explores the impact of human factors (personality and culture) and system factors (frame rate, resolution, and bit rate) on user affect and enjoyment of multimedia presentations. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Multimedia (cs.MM), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). However, given the focus on user affect and enjoyment, cs.HC and cs.MM are the most likely sub-categories.
